 courses , or private instruction to fit your needs. Contact us!       Online Course Descriptions, Schedules and Fees     Online Grammar         Course Info   This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the Blackboard learning management system to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from your instructor.  This course focuses on producing clear, error-free writing at the intermediate to advanced level. Your instructor will guide you through advanced grammar review, writing sample analysis, and development of effective self-editing techniques. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.  By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify weaknesses in your own and others’ writing  Make fewer errors in advanced grammatical structures  Use effective strategies for proofreading and editing your own work   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B : Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $400 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to enroll? Complete our online registration form.    Register for your course today          Online Writing and Composing         Course Info   This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the Blackboard learning management system to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from the instructor.  This course focuses on how to produce concise, clear writing at the intermediate to advanced level.  You will learn techniques for starting a writing project, working with outlines, creating clear paragraphs, crafting introductions and conclusions, and adding concrete details. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.  By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Improve both paragraph and document organization  Be more confident with starting, revising, and concluding your writing  Clearly communicate ideas in a professionally written document   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Fee  $400 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.    Register for your course today          Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening         Course Info   This 5-week course focuses on learning the test-taking strategies necessary for succeeding on the Reading and Listening sections of the TOEFL iBT.  Self-paced presentations teach you test strategies, and your instructor assigns detailed practice exercises and provides individualized weekly feedback and advice.  In this course, you are able to work at your own pace reviewing presentations, studying vocabulary, and completing practice exercises and tests.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for answering each of the question types on the Reading and Listening sections of the test  Study vocabulary necessary for the TOEFL iBT test  Complete practice exercises and take numerous practice tests  Receive individualized instructor advice and guidance  Receive individualized instructor advice and guidance   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify types of questions that you are struggling with and apply strategies to answer these questions correctly  Improve your academic vocabulary  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $350  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Required Textbooks  You must purchase the textbook for this course on your own before the course starts. You have two options:  You can purchase these two separate textbooks (one for each skill):   Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL test: iBT Reading (text with CD-ROM)  Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL Test: iBT Listening (text with Audio CDs CD-ROM)   Or, you can purchase the following single textbook (all skills):  Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL test: iBT (text with CD-ROM)    Register for your course today          Online TOEFL Prep: Writing         Course Info   This 5-week course combines grammar and writing instruction to help you prepare for the Writing section of the TOEFL iBT test. Course documents provide a review of problematic grammar concepts in order to help you produce error-free sentences, while self-paced presentations teach you about the appropriate content and organization of each of the two TOEFL Writing tasks. Every week, you will be asked to write one essay, and you will receive individualized feedback and advice from the instructor.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for responding to each of the two writing tasks  Study writing templates and useful phrases  Complete practice tasks and take a final writing practice test  Receive individualized instructor feedback and advice   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Improve the organization, content, and accuracy of your essays  Identify weaknesses in your writing and correct your own errors  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $400  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for your course today          Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking         Course Info   This 4-week course focuses on learning the test-taking strategies necessary to succeed on the Speaking section of the TOEFL iBT.  Self-paced presentations teach you test strategies for each of the six TOEFL Speaking tasks, while speech templates help you organize and deliver an appropriate response. In this course, you work at your own pace reviewing presentations and sample speaking tasks and responses, and every week, you submit two recorded TOEFL Speaking responses to the instructor for individualized feedback and advice.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for responding to each of the six speaking tasks  Study speaking templates and listen to sample responses  Complete practice tasks and take a final speaking practice test  Receive individualized instructor feedback and advice   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify the speaking task types and know what is required to complete each task  Improve the organization, content, and clarity of your responses  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 7  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – March 28  Summer Term A: May 29 – June 26  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 7   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $350  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for your course today          Online TOEFL Prep – Complete Course Package         Course Info   If you need to improve your score in all 4 TOEFL sections, enroll in our complete course package (Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening, Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking, and Online TOEFL Prep: Writing) for a reduced tuition fee of $1,000 (a $100 discount). You can take these courses together in one semester or separately over three consecutive semesters.  Course Fee  $1,000  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for your course today              Ready to enroll?  Register for your Online Course today      Not sure what you need?  Request a free language assessment           Request More Information  Contact us to learn more about our online courses.   Request Info            Other Programs    Back to main content           English for International Professionals    Test Prep Courses    Online Courses    Chicago, Communication and Culture    Customized Programs    Tutoring & Editing    Testing Services                  UIC Logo        The Tutorium         Main Menu    Intensive English    Other Programs    Student Life    About Us    How to Apply      IEP    IEP Courses    IEP Tuition & Fees    IEP Start Dates    Pay Fees    Current Students      More Info    I-20 & Visa    English for International Professionals    Contact Us        Quick Links    Request Information    Apply    Pay Fees         Contact   Tutorium in Intensive English  1333 South Halsted Street, Suite 260 Chicago, Illinois 60607-5019 USA  Phone: +1-312-996-8098  Fax: +1-312-996-4394  tutorium@uic.edu        Social Media Acco